The building  structure of DL app
Create a complete full-stack hybrid mobile application called:
Downtown Lobby Beta Version: 0.2
Package Name: com.downtownlobby.khs
By: Main Studios
The system must be built in two phases:
Backend + Admin Panel (FIRST)
Frontend Hybrid Android App (SECOND)
🧠 CORE CONCEPT
Downtown Lobby is a modern school digital platform where students can access announcements, events, news, timetables, and entertainment content — all dynamically controlled from a web-based admin panel.
All content must come from the backend. Nothing should be hardcoded in the app.
🔧 PHASE 1: BACKEND + ADMIN PANEL
Backend Requirements
Build a custom backend using:
Node.js (Express.js recommended) OR
Supabase-style backend (auto-managed DB + storage)
Core Features:
📊 Database Collections:
Announcements
Events
News & Posts
Timetable (image-based)
Videos (Entertainment)
App Version Control
📁 Storage System:
Upload images (posts, timetable)
Upload videos (for streaming)
Store PDFs (optional support)
♻️ Smart Cleanup System (IMPORTANT):
When admin deletes:
A post → delete its image from storage
A video → remove file completely
A timetable → replace old file
This prevents storage overflow and keeps backend optimized.
⚡ API System:
Create REST API endpoints:
GET /announcements
GET /events
GET /posts
GET /videos
GET /timetable
GET /app-version
All data must be dynamically fetched by the app.
🖥️ Admin Panel (Web Dashboard)
Create a modern admin dashboard with login authentication.
Admin must be able to:
📢 Create/Edit/Delete Announcements
📅 Manage Events
📰 Manage News & Posts
🖼 Upload & Replace Timetable (Weekly + Exam)
🎬 Upload/Delete Videos
📄 Upload PDFs (optional)
🚀 Update App Version + APK Download Link
🔔 Remote Update System (IMPORTANT)
Admin panel must include:
Version number input (e.g. 0.2 → 0.3)
APK download link field
Backend stores:
latest_version
update_message
download_url
